race.comment: LUPIN D'ETE (13) came home 3L clear of his rivals tackling Class D level at Vichy. Taken to complete a double dropping in grade. LAO DE NAPPES (2) followed up a nose win in a Class F event at Chateauroux with a neck second racing at Carpentras. Expected to play a leading role. LOULOU DU SABLIER (8) is the winner of two of his last three starts including by 1.75L when contesting a lower graded event at Lyon-Parilly. Strong claims of delivering the fourth success of his career. LEADER RASTID (7) left an early DQ behind him securing a 2L victory at Hyeres. Notable contender making his first appearance at this circuit.
